# Medical Records - AI:CML Example

This document demonstrates AI:CML format for healthcare data, showing
how to organize patient records, diagnoses, and treatment information
while maintaining privacy and structure.

Note: All data in this example is fictional and for demonstration only.

DICT aliases
  cardio: Cardiovascular System
  resp: Respiratory System
  neuro: Neurological System
  endo: Endocrine System
  ortho: Orthopedic System
END

DICT conditions
  htn: Hypertension (High Blood Pressure)
  t2dm: Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus
  cad: Coronary Artery Disease
  asthma: Asthma
  copd: Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease
END

DICT medications
  metformin: Metformin (Diabetes medication)
  lisinopril: Lisinopril (Blood pressure medication)
  atorvastatin: Atorvastatin (Cholesterol medication)
  albuterol: Albuterol (Bronchodilator)
  aspirin: Aspirin (Antiplatelet agent)
END

