## Clinical Queries

QUERY HighRiskPatients
  SELECT id, age, conditions, bmi
  FROM ENTITY Patient
  WHERE bmi > 28 AND age > 60
  ORDER BY age DESC
END

QUERY DiabeticPatients
  SELECT id, age, medications
  FROM ENTITY Patient
  WHERE conditions CONTAINS @t2dm
END

QUERY ElevatedBloodPressure
  SELECT PatientID, Date, SystolicBP, DiastolicBP
  FROM ROW VitalSigns_November2024
  WHERE SystolicBP > 140 OR DiastolicBP > 90
END

QUERY UpcomingAppointments
  SELECT PatientID, Date, Time, Provider
  FROM ROW Appointments_December2024
  WHERE Status = Scheduled
  ORDER BY Date ASC
END

QUERY AbnormalLabResults
  SELECT PatientID, Glucose, HbA1c, Cholesterol
  FROM ROW LabResults_Q4_2024
  WHERE Glucose > 125 OR HbA1c > 6.5 OR Cholesterol > 200
END

## Clinical Notes

This medical records database demonstrates how AI:CML can structure
healthcare information for efficient retrieval and analysis. The alias
system reduces token usage by defining medical terms once and reusing
them throughout patient records.

The embedded queries enable quick identification of at-risk patients,
medication tracking, and appointment management without requiring
separate database queries or external systems.

Privacy Note: In production systems, patient data would be encrypted
and access-controlled. This example uses fictional data for
demonstration purposes only.
